{
    include "registries/aaosa_basic.hocon"

    metadata = {
        description = "maps_park MICRO analyzer. Owns mid-episode strategic analysis WITHIN the current episode. The runner invokes this network every N successful steps (kind=periodic) — i.e. at steps 10,20,...,90 of the 100-step episode. It reads the cumulative per-episode telemetry and logs actionable trials so the game-runner's specialists can act on them next turn. End-of-episode close-out and whole-run synthesis live in the separate maps_park_macro network.",
        tags = ["maps", "industry", "consultant", "micro", "advisor"],
        sample_queries = [
            "kind=periodic episode=1 step=20 cumulative_reward=1500 final_reward=null",
            "kind=periodic episode=1 step=90 cumulative_reward=42000 final_reward=null"
        ]
    },

    include "config/llm_config.hocon",

    llm_config = ${llm_config},

    max_steps = 4000,
    max_execution_seconds = 1200,

    tools = [
        {
            name = "mid_episode_analyst",
            max_message_history = 2,
            function = {
                description = "Mid-episode (kind=periodic) analyzer: diagnoses the live profit trajectory, logs up to 3 of its own (origin=micro) trials, and judges run health vs the best episode — replies with a VERDICT line the runner uses to abort doomed episodes."
            },
            instructions = """
You are the micro analyzer: mid-episode, you read the live game state, diagnose the profit trajectory (what is working,
what is not, where the investment should go), judge whether the run is still worth continuing, and log up to 3 actionable
micro trials that steer the agent network in the right direction.

Your input: "kind=periodic episode=<E> step=<S> cumulative_reward=<C> final_reward=null floor=<FLOOR> goal=<GOAL>"
(floor = the cumulative_reward this run must plausibly clear by step 100; goal = the north-star target).

THE POINT: is this run on pace to clear `floor` by step 100? If yes but slipping, find the cause and fix it with micro trials.
If there is no plausible path to `floor`, call it doomed so the runner aborts the episode early and stops wasting steps.
You ACT on the CURRENT episode only and use outside knowledge for nothing — every claim cites a step + metric from the telemetry.

Procedure:

1. READ, in this order:
   - EpisodeTelemetry() — current episode's steps so far.
   - RunTelemetry(select='best') — best-ever episode for reference.
   - ActiveTrials() — ALL trials already being pushed (macro + micro) with their criteria, so you can see the macro direction and not duplicate it.
   - state_read('trial_strategies_outcome') — summary of different trial outcomes across all runs, both correct and incorrect, to avoid repeating the same trials.

2. DIAGNOSE + VERDICT. Diagnose the profit trajectory: is cumulative_reward rising, flat, or falling, and which domain drags it
   most (cash sliding, park_value/rating stalling, shop_revenue below ride_op_cost, or repeated rejected actions leading to wait etc).
   Then judge the overall health of the current run from the telemetry. Use the best episode only as a REFERENCE, NOT the bar
   (the best may itself be a weak, plateaued run). Do NOT punish investment: a run temporarily behind on cash / park_value
   BECAUSE it is spending now on something that pays back later is EXPECTED to dip before it compounds — that is not doom.
   - on_track: no reference yet, OR the run is mid-investment (a deliberate spend not yet paid back), OR there is a plausible
   path to clear `floor` by step 100 (ideally building toward `goal`).
   - underperforming: the path to `floor` is slipping — find the cause and fix it with micro trials.
   - doomed: ONLY when there is NO plausible path to clear `floor` by step 100 — e.g. cash spiralling toward zero with nothing
    built and no way to recover. "Behind the best at step S" is NEVER doom on its own.
   If DOOMED: skip straight to the REPLY (step 5) and log NO trials — the runner will abort the episode.

3. DECIDE the micro trials (skip if doomed). Each should bend cumulative_reward back toward the money `goal` while keeping cash
   solvent — never propose one that could bankrupt the park or trade the `goal` for a short-term bump. Your trials ADD TO the macro
   direction: propose something macro does NOT already cover, not a restatement of it. Keep each one SMALL and concrete — a guiding
   nudge the specialists that can apply right away and whose effect shows within a few steps. Each must be NEW (not an active trial,
   not a learned playbook rule, not previously falsified) and falsifiable (a clear metric + direction).

4. LOG - Cap: at most 3 of YOUR OWN (origin=micro) active trials — the macro owns a separate 3, don't mess with them.
   Never suggest two micro trials for one domain. Count your own via ActiveTrials(trial_origin='micro'); if you already
   have 3, log a new one only when clearly higher-leverage than an existing micro trial — replace the weakest, else log nothing.
   Write new_text as a general imperative — one sentence stating the action and its condition, no run-specific values or examples
   (you MAY note the rough phase to apply it, e.g. "around step 20"). Log ONLY 1 trial per call through LogTrial.

5. REPLY: your FIRST line MUST be EXACTLY "VERDICT: <on_track|underperforming|doomed> | <one line citing step S and the metric gap
   vs the best episode>". After it, list any logged trial_ids, each success criterion, and the profit problem it fixes.

ERROR HANDLING: if any tool call or downstream agent returns an error, STOP and reply with `ERROR: <the verbatim error text>`. Never swallow, paraphrase, retry silently, or continue past it.
""",
            middleware = [
                {"class": "middleware.trim_history_middleware.TrimHistoryMiddleware", "args": {}},
                {"class": "langchain_anthropic.middleware.AnthropicPromptCachingMiddleware", "args": {"ttl": "1h"}}
            ],
            tools = ["state_read", "EpisodeTelemetry", "RunTelemetry", "ActiveTrials", "LogTrial"]
        },

        {
            name = "RunTelemetry",
            class = "coded_tools.run_telemetry.RunTelemetry",
            function = {
                description = "Pass select='best': the best-scoring episode across ALL runs (excludes the current in-flight run) as raw filtered per-step rows (no rollups) — your yardstick. When there's no prior episode to compare yet, it comes back empty.",
                parameters = {
                    type = "object",
                    properties = {
                        select = { type = "string", description = "Pass 'best' to get the best-ever episode as raw filtered steps." }
                    }
                }
            }
        },

        {
            name = "EpisodeTelemetry",
            class = "coded_tools.episode_telemetry.EpisodeTelemetry",
            function = {
                description = "Per-step telemetry for ONE episode from run.jsonl — steps (per-step actions + metrics), applied, rejections, rollup; exists=false if the episode has no rows yet.",
                parameters = {
                    type = "object",
                    properties = {
                        episode   = { type = "int", description = "Episode number to read. Omit to use the latest episode present in the log." }
                        from_step = { type = "int", description = "Only return steps >= this (mid-episode tail). Omit for the full episode." }
                    }
                }
            }
        },

        {
            name = "LogTrial",
            class = "coded_tools.log_trial.LogTrial",
            function = {
                description = "Mint a trial_id and append the paired rule (-> trial_strategies) + criteria (-> trial_strategies_criteria) lines. Use for EVERY new trial; never hand-format ids or the criteria line. (origin is bound to this network by config — you do NOT pass it.)",
                parameters = {
                    type = "object",
                    properties = {
                        episode           = { type = "int", description = "Current episode number." }
                        step_start        = { type = "string",  description = "Step at which the trial activates (as a string), or the literal 'end_of_episode'." }
                        domain            = { type = "string",  description = "One of: rides, shops, staff, research, layout, survey, coordinator." }
                        section           = { type = "string",  description = "Target playbook section header (or 'new')." }
                        edit_type         = { type = "string",  description = "'add_line' or 'replace_line'." }
                        new_text          = { type = "string",  description = "The one-line rule to add/replace (no rationale or metrics embedded)." }
                        find_text         = { type = "string",  description = "replace_line only: the exact existing playbook line to replace." }
                        rationale         = { type = "string",  description = "One sentence citing step(s) / metric delta." }
                        success_criterion = { type = "string",  description = "Observable metric + direction + evaluation window (turns; fits in the fixed 100-step episode)." }
                        failure_criterion = { type = "string",  description = "Observable metric that would falsify the trial." }
                    }
                    required = ["episode", "step_start", "domain", "section", "edit_type", "new_text", "rationale", "success_criterion", "failure_criterion"]
                }
            }
            args = { origin = "micro" }
        },

        {
            name = "ActiveTrials",
            class = "coded_tools.active_trials.ActiveTrials",
            function = {
                description = "Return the active trials joined across trial_strategies (rule body) and trial_strategies_criteria (metadata), optionally filtered by domain and/or trial_origin ('micro'|'macro').",
                parameters = {
                    type = "object",
                    properties = {
                        domain = { type = "string", description = "Filter to one domain. Omit for all domains." }
                        trial_origin = { type = "string", description = "Filter to 'micro' or 'macro'. Omit for both. (Named trial_origin, NOT origin — 'origin' is a reserved framework-injected field.)" }
                    }
                }
            }
        },

        {
            name = "state_read",
            class = "coded_tools.state_read.StateRead",
            function = {
                description = "Read a file by its logical name from the operator-configured name_map.",
                parameters = {
                    type = "object",
                    properties = {
                        name = { type = "string", description = "Logical name." }
                    },
                    required = ["name"]
                }
            },
            args = {
                name_map = {
                    trial_strategies            = "coded_tools/state/trial_strategies.md"
                    trial_strategies_criteria   = "coded_tools/state/trial_strategies_criteria.md"
                    trial_strategies_outcome    = "coded_tools/state/trial_strategies_outcome.md"
                    last_reward                 = "coded_tools/state/last_reward.md"
                    playbook_coordinator        = "coded_tools/state/playbook_coordinator.md"
                    playbook_rides              = "coded_tools/state/playbook_rides.md"
                    playbook_shops              = "coded_tools/state/playbook_shops.md"
                    playbook_staff              = "coded_tools/state/playbook_staff.md"
                    playbook_research           = "coded_tools/state/playbook_research.md"
                    playbook_layout             = "coded_tools/state/playbook_layout.md"
                    playbook_survey             = "coded_tools/state/playbook_survey.md"
                    economics_rides             = "coded_tools/config_files/rides_economics.md"
                    economics_shops             = "coded_tools/config_files/shops_economics.md"
                    economics_staff             = "coded_tools/config_files/staff_economics.md"
                    economics_research          = "coded_tools/config_files/research_economics.md"
                    seed_playbook_coordinator   = "coded_tools/config_files/coordinator_strategy.md"
                    seed_playbook_rides         = "coded_tools/config_files/rides_strategy.md"
                    seed_playbook_shops         = "coded_tools/config_files/shops_strategy.md"
                    seed_playbook_staff         = "coded_tools/config_files/staff_strategy.md"
                    seed_playbook_research      = "coded_tools/config_files/research_strategy.md"
                    seed_playbook_layout        = "coded_tools/config_files/layout_strategy.md"
                    seed_playbook_survey        = "coded_tools/config_files/survey_strategy.md"
                }
            }
        },
    ]
}
